Create or reserve a Service Certificate resource

Without the optional csr query parameter, an X.509 certificate is generated and this is returned. If the csr query parameter is present, a Certificate Signing Request is instead generated and returned, allowing the X.509 certificate to be generated by the invoker and later uploaded.

Authorizations:
None
path Parameters
provisioningSessionId
required
string (ResourceId)

The resource identifier of an existing Provisioning Session.'

query Parameters
csr
boolean

When present, return a Certificate Signing Request instead of generating an X.509 certificate

Request Body schema: application/json

An optional list of domain name aliases to be included in the returned Certificate Signing Request

Array
string

Responses

/{apiRoot}/3gpp-maf-provisioning/v1/provisioning-sessions/%7bprovisioningSessionId%7d/certificates

required

string (BdtReferenceId)

string identifying a BDT Reference ID as defined in clause 5.3.3 of 3GPP TS 29.154.

object (BdtPolicySchedule)

Patch an Edge Resources Configuration for the specified Provisioning Session

Authorizations:
None
path Parameters
provisioningSessionId
required
string (ResourceId)

The resource identifier of an existing Provisioning Session.

edgeResourcesConfigurationId
required
string (ResourceId)

The resource identifier of an existing Edge Resources Configuration.

Request Body schema:
required

A JSON representation of a Edge Resources Configuration

required
string or string (EdgeManagementMode)

The management mode of an EAS.

object (EdgeProcessingEligibilityCriteria)
required
object (EASRequirements)

Requirements of an EAS.

object (M1EASRelocationRequirements)

Relocation requirements of an EAS.

Responses

/{apiRoot}/3gpp-maf-provisioning/v1/provisioning-sessions/%7bprovisioningSessionId%7d/edge-resources-configurations/%7bedgeResourcesConfigurationId%7d

Supply an Event Data Processing Configuration for the specified Provisioning Session

Authorizations:
None
path Parameters
provisioningSessionId
required
string (ResourceId)

The resource identifier of an existing Provisioning Session.

Request Body schema: application/json
required

A JSON representation of a Event Data Processing Configuration

required
string or string (AfEvent)

Represents an application's event.
Possible values are:

  • SVC_EXPERIENCE: Indicates that the subscribed/notified event is service experience information for an application.
  • UE_MOBILITY: Indicates that the subscribed/notified event is UE mobility information.
  • UE_COMM: Indicates that the subscribed/notified event is UE communication information.
  • EXCEPTIONS: Indicates that the subscribed/notified event is exceptions information.
  • USER_DATA_CONGESTION: Indicates that the subscribed/notified event is user data congestion analytics related information.
  • PERF_DATA: Indicates that the subscribed/notified event is performance data information.
  • DISPERSION: Indicates that the subscribed/notified event is dispersion information.
  • COLLECTIVE_BEHAVIOUR: Indicates that the subscribed/notified event is collective behaviour information.
  • MS_QOE_METRICS: Indicates that the subscribed/notified event is Media Streaming QoE metrics.
  • MS_CONSUMPTION: Indicates that the subscribed/notified event is Media Streaming consumption reports.
  • MS_NET_ASSIST_INVOCATION: Indicates that the subscribed/notified event is Media Streaming network assistance invocation.
  • MS_DYN_POLICY_INVOCATION: Indicates that the subscribed/notified event is Media Streaming dynamic policy invocation.
  • MS_ACCESS_ACTIVITY: Indicates that the subscribed/notified event is Media Streaming access activity.
  • GNSS_ASSISTANCE_DATA: Indicates that the subscribed/notified event is GNSS Assistance Data Collection.
authorizationUrl
string <uri> (AbsoluteUrl)

Absolute Uniform Resource Locator, conforming with the "absolute-URI" production specified in IETF RFC 3986, section 4.3 in which the scheme part is "http" or "https". Note that the "query" suffix is permitted by this production but the "fragment" suffix is not.

required
Array of objects (DataAccessProfile)
